summary:
HANDWRITING CAN TELL YOU A LOT ABOUT A PERSON. 
go here and repost with your character’s name in their handwriting! 
Tagged by...
body:
HANDWRITING CAN TELL YOU A LOT ABOUT A PERSON.

go here and repost with your character’s name in their handwriting!

Tagged by @diversiformheros​

Tagging- Whoever wants to do it. Especially @diversiformheros (Do Di and Eddie!), and if they haven’t done it yet, @zzapzzaptasers and @nomadshield and @araedi

Bucky first-

Before the war- he takes pride in his penmanship. He struggled almost his entire childhood with mastering learning to read, due to his dyslexia and the little understanding of how to work with that at the time. 

During his time in Red Room, he was Kolya, the Asset. He was about efficiency, speed, and concise communication. 

After he began to regain his memories, he struggled with trying to regain his prettier style. It didn’t go well, and he still struggles with it, especially because of the tremors he has some days. Cursive makes his eyes go blurry, anymore, so a middling smooshed half and half lettering develops. 

Then, people started wanting autographs. Wanting his signature, something stylized. Fancy but fast. And the Winter Soldier style drifted to something more artistic. Brutal, fast, but something that looks nothing like The Asset. 

When he gets teased about his gang lettering, he gets a chance to blow Clint’s mind, by informing him and anyone else that cares to ask, that yes, he and Steve were part of a gang- it just was more a paper delivery gang than a drugs and illicit materials gang… though Steve did art for Bluies…

Tony however has evolved the other way- 

When living up to the ideal son, and straining so hard for approval- 

However in MIT that changed, dramatically. 

Then- then Tony breaks free. Ze knows Jarvis would want his wife’s name to live on, and honestly anything to further say fuck you to Howard and any and all of Howard’s choices. Including every curlie swishy bit of frippery ze can pack into a signature “because fuck you Howard, I am an adult and I can.” 

Also, “never knew my mother, but hey, I’ll go by her name as it’s better than Stark.” is totally a reason to go by that last name.
